## 7. Coding Rules (Cursor-Enforced)

- Views must NOT:
  - Fetch data directly
  - Contain business logic
- ViewModels must:
  - Be annotated with `@MainActor`
  - Expose state via `@Published`
- Repositories must:
  - Be protocol-based
  - Be dependency-injected
  - Avoid singletons

---

## 8. Naming Conventions

- Views: `FeatureNameView`
- ViewModels: `FeatureNameViewModel`
- Repositories: `FeatureRepository`
- Services: `FeatureService`

---

## 9. Extensibility Rules

- Each feature must:
  - Live under `Features/`
  - Have its own View and ViewModel
  - Reuse Core services
- Shared UI components belong in `Shared/Components`

---

## 10. MVP Success Criteria

- Event creation < 60 seconds
- RSVP flow < 10 seconds
- Guest check-in works offline
- No crashes during normal flows
